EaglePage *  source1,
EaglePage *  source2,
void *  obj 
)

Calculate values in a page that are greater than an integer.

This function does not allocate memory.

Parameters:
[in] destination Must be preallocated to the same size as page. All records in this page will be given a value or 0 or 1 based on the result of the comparison.
[in] source1 The page to scan, can be any size.
[in] source2 Ignored.
[in] obj Must be int* which is dereferenced to the integer value for comparison.
See also:
